    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Could this logic be extracted out of the production code and into the `pytest` package? It also seems like it could be much simpler if it wrapped the existing `newPty()` func. Maybe something like\n\n```\n  func New(t *testing.T, opts ...pty.Option) *PTY {\n      t.Helper()\n\n      acquireSemaphore(t) \n\n      ptty, err := newTestPTY(opts...)\n      if err != nil {\n          releaseSemaphore()\n          require.NoError(t, err)\n      }\n\n      // ... existing setup ...\n\n      t.Cleanup(func() {\n          _ = r.Close()\n          releaseSemaphore() \n      })\n      return r\n  }\n```",
    "commit_id": "47687fd4be80bc0fd8795efd2718630ec6adb29a",
